	rn how to embroider fruits using 3 beginner embroidery stitches. This clas
	s is great for kids looking to get started with hand embroidery. They’ll l
	earn how to place their fabric in the hoop\\\, transfer the pattern\\\, sp
	lit apart their thread\\\, and stitch the satin stitch\\\, back stitch\\\,
	 and sead stitch. Each attendee will receive a full kit that includes: a w
	ooden embroidery hoop\\\, fruit transfer designs\\\, an embroidery needle\
	\\, full skeins of embroidery thread\\\, cream cotton fabric\\\, and print
	ed instructions.\n\nhttps://myballard.com/event/kids-embroidery-class-frui
