BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:8z2NlcNXAmSDTJJ8XzcAk
SUMMARY:Mother's Day Native Art Market
DTSTAMP:20260308T025645Z
DTSTART:20260509T100000Z
DESCRIPTION:FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE – February 10\\\, 2026\\nMEDIA ADVISORY: 
	CELEBRATE MOTHER’S DAY BY SUPPORTING LOCAL INDIGENOUS ARTISANS AT THE NATI
	VE ART MARKET \\nCONTACT: SiSi Campbell\\\, scampbell@unitedindians.org\\\
	, 206.496.4007\\nWHEN: Saturday\\\, May 9th & Sunday\\\, May 10th\\\, 2026
	 | 10:00 AM – 5:00 PM\\nWHERE: Daybreak Star Indian Cultural Center\\\, 50
	11 Bernie Whitebear Way\\\, Seattle\\\, WA 98199 (Located in Discovery Par
	k)\\nWHAT: This Mother’s Day weekend\\\, the United Indians of All Tribes 
	Foundation hosts the Native Art Market. Native Art Market. Featuring authe
	ntic masterworks from over 30 Indigenous artisans\\\, the market offers a 
	unique opportunity to find one-of-a-kind gifts while directly supporting t
	he local Native economy. Every piece is represented in accordance with the
	 Indian Arts and Crafts Act of 1990\\\, ensuring your purchase honors and 
	supports Indigenous creators.\\nWHY: By bridging the gap between Indigenou
	s creators and the public\\\, this event provides a platform for artists t
	o thrive while promoting economic self-determination. Choosing to ‘Buy Nat
	ive’ allows attendees to support Indigenous entrepreneurs during a critica
	l time for the local community and economy\\\, ensuring that Native owned 
	brands continue to preserve their history and culture.\\n# # #\\nAbout Uni
	ted Indians of All Tribes Foundation (UIATF): UIATF provides vital social\
	\\, educational\\\, and cultural services to the Native community in the P
	uget Sound region. The Daybreak Star Indian Cultural Center serves as a co
	rnerstone for these efforts\\\, acting as a hub for cultural rejuvenation 
	and community connection. For more information\\\, visit unitedindians.org
	.\n\nhttps://myballard.com/event/mothers-day-native-art-market/\n\nFrom My
	 Ballard
URL:https://myballard.com/event/mothers-day-native-art-market/
LOCATION:WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:myballard
CATEGORIES:My Ballard
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT31H
END:VEVENT
